From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Electron Scripts <scripts@electron>
Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2026 15:42:27 +0200
Subject: src: include <cstdlib> for abort() in builtin_info.cc
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

builtin_info.cc calls abort() but only includes builtin_info.h,
which transitively pulls in <cinttypes>/<string>/<unordered_map>
/<vector> — none of which guarantee <cstdlib> is visible.
upstream Node builds tolerate this due to implicit inclusion, but
Electron's stricter Chromium-style build fails with "use of
undeclared identifier 'abort'". Add the explicit include.

This patch can be removed when upstream Node adds the include.

diff --git a/src/builtin_info.cc b/src/builtin_info.cc
index d5309265ac373310c20ba4f2438a778c9753254a..d4767b2c49538751ac0a877969764733401e498d 100644
--- a/src/builtin_info.cc
+++ b/src/builtin_info.cc
@@ -1,5 +1,7 @@
 #include "builtin_info.h"
 
+#include <cstdlib>
+
 namespace node {
 namespace builtins {
 
